I love this venue a lot. theres a very nice feeling. The cuisine is great. the service is powerful and the waiters are very professional. The cost is decent. extremely recommend.
Good concept

2nd trip to Onsen and even better than the first! Excellent food! Crab and steamed egg mushroom soufflé-type dish was phenomenal!! Lamb skewer incredibly succulent. Great atmosphere and service. Highly recommend this place. Neighborhood not great, I'd advise to take an Uber to and from the front door at night.
Bath house is amazing. Staff is always friendly. The only thing I wish they’d do is to enforce silence. Sometimes the bathhouse can get loud...

Ridiculously expensive restaurant. The food is good but far from exceptional and incredibly pricey, and you don't even get to be full for that price.  The skewers are 15$ and you got two little pieces of steak. Very pretentious.
Great japanese-american fusion food and nice vibe.
Bathhouse + dinner was an amazing experience. The food was very tasty, especially the Okonomiyaki.
The food was sensational!
Delicious food- great baths! Make sure you get some dumplings.

The unexpected highlight of our vacation. I'm a tough critic but this place deserves 5 stars and more. We followed the website's recommendation and booked our bath for 2 hours before dinner. We arrived 15 minutes late AND had made the …

The facility is nice, but small. 12 people chatted around a 5*5 feet hot pool, slammed the doors coming in and out of the sauna and steam room. It was loud and cramped. The employees didn't do anything to remind the guests to speak quietly. It is a nice hot tab, but not an onsen experience.

This review is for the bathhouse, not the restaurant (which is probably great).  "Onsen" is a rather inappropriate description of this bathhouse. This place is a "pool party". People completely ignore the greeter's request, and multiple …

Bath: Beautiful facility, very clean and artistically designed. The steam room is intense (in a good way)! I was disappointed by a few things though. The bath is in need of a cold pool; I would much rather dunk in a cold pool instead of …

I was sorely disappointed.  The baths are fine and the facility  is nice, but expect lots of chit chat about tech. It was ok, but I won't return. Spend you money on the Kabuki or the Banya if you want a soot

Perfect place to relax. The environment is gorgeous, a small Japanese gem in the hearth or San Francisco. The staff is kind and they provide you everything (from swimsuit to hot tea). I rate It 4 and not 5 only because it's all indoor …

The bath here is amazing. One rate place that encouraged me to hold still long enough to breathe deeply. Alternating the 118 degree steam or dry sauna with cold plunge or pool was perfect. Hot tea to pair is delightful.  The food for dinner …
too expansive !! ,the dishes was very small , we came out of there hungry

I am 7ft tall and this little place is a God seits. This little place is always super clean, fresh smelling and the staff is awesome and super cool.. it's not your sleazy bathhouse like the ones on van ness used to be.. space is limited  as …

This is the most relaxed I have been in years! I'm on my feet for 8-10 hours per day and after an evening here my daily pain was down to almost nothing. The food is EXCELLENT as well. The dishes are creative and unique as well as delicious. …
Delicious, excellent, new dishes from this very streamlined kitchen. Great service. Terrific sake list and expert guidance.

This is a lovely little bath house. Beautifully decorated. We booked an 11am appointment for 3 people. In total there were about 9 people using the facilities during our reservation. Extremely clean and well maintained. Towels, robes and …

Nice little place that we stumbled upon. Every dish we had was delicious and reasonable. I especially love the lamb skewers. Some of the best in the Bay. The okonomiyaki is also an interesting take on that dish that I haven't tasted before. Definitely worth a visit. Reservation is a must.

Beautiful, clean, relaxing! This was an Oasis in the middle of a busy Wednesday afternoon. Very simple baths with hot tub, dry sauna, and steam sauna. The decor is gorgeous and the bathroom toilet has heating features, bidet, and a host of …

If you are health conscious or just wanted to have a relaxing time, this one is for you! All facilities are clean and well maintained. I just love the fact that even if i visited this place for a number of time already, every time i visit everything is clean.

Really nice design and facilities, but my experienced was somewhat ruined by my fellow patrons. They were overly talkative, making loud noises, dunking themselves in and out of the water... total vibe killer. I think the staff could solve this by simply reminding guests the rules of the road.
Amazing bathhouse with amenities. Worth the price, which is friendly to any budget.
The baths are a true respite in SF’s heart of darkness.

Absolutely beautiful bathhouse. Unfortunately it's not in the best part of the city so if your out of town I suggest using Uber or Lyft to get here. It is well worth the cost of the ride. They have a steam room, sauna, warm pool and even a Japanese Toto toilet in the restroom.
This is our favorite place in the city! Have a drink soak away!
Dishes are extremely small
Quality service, great atmosphere, excellent food.  Great spot for a date night.

Wow the service here was absolutely fantastic. Friendly, excellent suggestions, and truly a wonderful evening.  My favorite was the butter popcorn desert and the tea was tasty and had a beautiful presentation. A lovely evening.
Ok for coed soaking if Kabuki Spa is inconvenient or if you can't get out of the city to a natural hot springs.
Relaxing bathhouse with a small hot pool, steam room, and a sauna. The restaurant is highly recommended too, make sure to book separately. Note that the neighborhood is sketchy.
Someting small but tayste just try it!!!!
Very relaxing and clean. Felt like a little piece of Japan here in SF

The food was great. Sad that you need a bouncer at the door but the area is shady at best.  I loved everything except maybe for the egg custard. It wasn't very savory. The trout sashimi was so good. I love ponzu. The steak was really good. …
Small menu with delicious options. Wontons, sashimi and a cup of dry sake are a must have.
They make magic in a tiny space. Fish dishes and dumplings have been consistently delicious. Try the cake.

Nice and clean bath facilities, with hot pool area, dry hot room and steam room. Would recommend a visit to unwind if you are predisposed to such facilities. Located in the tenderloin so plan travel accordingly. Well worth a visit for something different.
Had an amazing dinner—the sardine skewers were killer! Afterwards I got to soak and sauna, and it was rad.
I enjoyed the evening. The Onsen experience was fun. The food was decent. I liked the mushroom dumplings a lot. I wish the rest of the menu had been as good.

Had a great visit. The soak and then dinner was a great combo. Everyone was one a couples date except for me but that was OK. The food was delicious. Located in the middle of the Tenderloin there are definite stark contrasts between the look and feel inside the Onsen and the surrounding neighborhood. Relaxing experience.

There is only one place better to eat than ONSEN Bath & Restaurant... that my fiend is Japan itself. This scrumptious sanctuary is a perfect realization of art, peace and nurturing. A “Zen Yakatori” if you will. I can only scratch the surface in the quality of food, preparation and plating. THIS IS THE REAL DEAL FOOD FOR LIFE.
The food was "out of bounds!!" The ambience was perfect for a party of 1 to 4. The sake was good, but the food made ALL the difference!!
Incredible dumplings & dessert.
Wonderful experience combined with dinner. The food is great and reasonably priced.
Very cool bathhouse for a group or solo. Sauna, steam room, hot tub, and ice cold shower (plus normal warm showers).
A little expensive but cozy place. Food is good especially the lamb skewers. Love the environment and dessert.
Trout sashimi worth tasting
Saunas are very well kept and perfect for relaxing. Server helped us pick the best combination of dishes and he was spot on!
Beautiful place and lovely, timely service. Had a really great time in the bath for my bachelorette.
Very nice food. The (semi) private rooms ARE a nice quiet oasis.
Great service and author's cuisine

The wait staff will clean your table before you're anywhere near ready to leave; raking things off the table above your lap. Also, our waitress came over at point and was chewing a mouthful of food. The food was great; the experience, not so much.

AVOID. I have gone here twice and both times have contracted Pseudomonas Folliculitis (a nasty itchy rash that comes from swimming in contaminated water). I have frequented many bathhouses and have never had this issue. It is relaxing in the moment but the horrible itching rash for a week afterward is not worth it.
Delicious as always. Great food and great sake.Love Onsen.
Very intimate dining experience. Beautiful atmosphere with amazing food!! The lamb skewers were melt in your mouth!!
Reservation policy is ridiculous. Not recommended.

Food is so so. Ambiance is great.
Love this onsen! Very relaxing place and facilities are well maintained. There's Max of 9 guests at anytime which makes it a perfect place to relax without feeling crowded.
Super relaxing. Great date spot!

Come for the bathhouse, stay for the delicious Japanese food. Unique place in SF (and Tenderloin) to unwind, relax, and have a solid meal.  Ask for counter seats if you want to see the magic that goes on in the kitchen and grill.
Authentic Japanese food in a nice setting. Good selection of sake and teas. Highly recommended.
Service are very remarkable. Price r great. it is if you can afford the check.
Great little onsen in the heart of Tenderloin with a Michelin star quality food. Owners are lovely people.

Beautiful restaurant with simple, delicious dishes! Tisanes were really soothing too.

Wonderful Japanese tapas in a cozy space right at the heart of the city. The dishes were super creative and flavourful. Def. would come back.

Great food and service.

A great bath house. I didn't try the food but the bath house is a wonderful escape from the city life. I would recommend making a reservation to ensure you're able to get in.

This place is amazing!!! What a gem! I have never been to a bath house before and after this I’m addicted. The food was incredible and I loved the cocktails. Service was wonderful as well! Definitely going back a bunch.

Onsen is restaurant, bathhouse, and hidden gem in the Tenderloin. I recommend booking a soak followed by dinner. The onsen itself is rather small, but extremely clean and well decorated. There is a sauna, steam room, soaking tub, cold …
Massage, spa or dining you can't miss with this place
Their Black Cod is my favorite
Was it worth it? A resounding no. Typical SF hipster place that enjoy overpriced dishes. Food is reasonable good but portions are way too small. At least give out some rice!
The spa was very cool, not incredible. I think could have felt more exclusive. The restaurant however, was fantastic. Overall 5 star experience (evening of spa and restaurant)
Delicious. Not too loud. The bathhouse might fun to do.
Amazing staff and wonderful food

Food is great and interesting, portions are small and you'll need to order 4-5 dishes for a good meal. Service is OK, but not very pleasant and welcoming, no sitting with back support. Good experience overall. Didn't visit the bath.
Soooooo goooooood. I think this is the best Izakaya in town. Worth walking through the Tenderloin.

I went for both a soak and dinner and enjoyed both! The bath house was a little more crowded than I expected but all of the amenities were lovely. They definitely had the most steamiest steam room I have ever been in. Dinner was fantastic …
Delicious food, lovely onsen
This is a beautiful bathhouse and restaurant. It's our go to date night spot!
Excellent way to spend Sundays. I'd recommend eating before going into the Onsen.
Some really good izakaya foods at this small restaurant.
You gotta go to the bath house prior to dinner. It's the only way to go

Impressive quality of food, drink, and service. Love the music selection too.

I've been to both the bathhouse and restaurant. The bathhouse is small, but nice. Locker rooms are very cramped, but the sauna, steam room and bath itself didn't feel overly crowded. Definitely make a reservation in advance.  I love the …

This restaurant / Japanese bathhouse isn't in the greatest area and the restaurant is a little cramped. However, the food is excellent, quite unique, and the menu changes regularly. Some favorites included the uni custard, sunchoke gyoza, smelt skewers, and mushroom dumplings.
No seat for one, even though it was room...
Incredible interior design. Food is reasonably tasty, but for the price the portions are a bit small.
Pretty good but slightly off on seasoning
Amazing food and drink and spa and service. Love this place.

Didn't go to the restaurant but went to the spa in the back. It is a must visit place in SF. So relaxing and bougie but in a great way. For the experience you get, I think it's worth it to go, but I would go on a Saturday morning when it's only $20
Tasty food and great service!

Onsen may have been the best part of my trip to San Francisco. It's has a menu of Japanese-inspired small plates that are absolutely delicious. But of course, Onsen is not just a restaurant. It's a fully functional Japanese onsen …

Love the decor, very trendy, but the ambiance isn't quite right for an Onsen. It's pretty loud (people are allowed to chat and they really do) and there's not enough seating to be comfy. However - the fact that you can talk makes it good for groups if you want to make a day of it!
It’s hard to find😵😵😵environment is awesome, food is honest to the price. I personally like small dishes:)
Loved the baths and the amazing Japanese food. The staff is wonderful. Will be back very soon!!!
Great spa and great food/Service. The mushroom dumplings are awesome!!!
Think traditional Japanese Bath house then this is your place. Clean, great service and a good place to escape from the daily grind. But beware of the parking situation.

This review is for the spa only. Great clean space. There are only three amenities: plunge pool, wet steam, and dry sauna.  All very well executed.  Please don't compare it to a Burke Spa or any resort spa.  It's a very traditional Japanese bath house.
Great place exciting news flavors. I'll be back.

The food was great but a bit pricy. The bath experience was wonderful. It really is a great deal for around $35 for almost 2 hours in the bath/sauna/steam room/showers. Lovely environment, but wish they'd crack down on the noise. Two women would not shut up.
Food was fantastic.
Spa is nice and relaxing. Space is bit too small and near Tenderloin. Not a very safe area to walk in. Service is great.
Food is very unique. Egg custard uni was excellent
Creative place, offering Japanese bath and massage services with interesting menu choices.
Awesome co-ed bath with a soaking tub, steam room, and dry sauna. Great natural light and plants on the brick wall gives it a nice vibe.

This is a rating for the bath house. It was lovely. Very relaxing and clean. The main bath was a good temperature and the steam room/sauna were relaxing. It was a bit on the smaller side, but I think they limit reservations, so it didn't feel crowded. We would definitely return.

This is for both the Onsen experience and for the dinner there  Onsen itself is on the small side but big enough to accommodate 8-10 people without feeling too cramped. I found the steam room a bit too hot for my liking, but the hot tub was …
I went there for a communal bath. It was cool. You can enjoy unlimited tea, water, pool, sauna, hammam, Japanese toilets. I found the water of the pool a bit to hot though.
Nice little spa in the middle of the Tenderloin. Food was overpriced.
So so good. The food tasted like heaven, the place is small and beautiful and the staff is really nice and polite.

Beautiful, recently-opened space tucked in the back of this restaurant. The combination of hot pool, steam room, Himalayan salt sauna and cold shower make for an extremely relaxing 2-hour experience. Will come back every time I visit SF.
This place rules. The couple that runs it is so friendly and sweet. The tea and atmosphere is phenomenal - what a Tenderloin gem! Really digging that this place exists.

This place is absolutely amazing! The decor is beautiful, the food was great and the staff was friendly and attentive.
Great atmosphere. Not too large.
A beautiful experience with delicious food and tea! Very impressive!
Service is unprofessional, but the bath is relaxing.
Tiny little spa with a great sauna, steam room and bath. Great for relaxing and a beautiful Japanese tea afterwards
Beautiful new Japanese bath, friendly staff, nice facilities, really hot Sauna and steam baths - I'll be back!

Really great concept + beautifully designed. The baths are a little pricy considering you don't get all the amenities of a full spa. Essentially there is a hot tub (couldn't turn on the jets), a stream room + a sauna. Steam room is small …

Phenomenal Japanese-style baths. Incredible Japanese food - and great service. I am in love with this place. After work, I love going to a bath, then having a great dinner. Massage and acupuncture, I'm told are coming!
Amazing!!!
Amazing spa environment attached to a restaurant serving premium teas and delicious Japanese inspired cuisine.
